My second Rmd document

Author: Myself

Last update: 26 Nov 2018

This is a sample .Rmd file, which will investigate the built-in R dataset containing the average monthly temperatures in Nottingham (in Farenheights).

1 The dataset

This is a random built-in dataset from R, I didn’t even know it existed. It has average monthly temperatures between 1920 and 1939.

2 Some plots

2.1 A boxplot

This was trickier than I expected. Since the plotFrame dataset is all numeric, if we simply call geom_boxplot() and ask for months on the x axis, it thinks that the scale is continuous. So it was necessary to convert x=as.factor(Month) in the aes() plot call in order to get the desired results.
